

1) install nodejs
2) install virtual environment
3) move the .env variables


-----
# Depeneding on the way with clone or fork the repo you may have different names

# the below assumes that you have changed the name of the repo in PersonalWebsite
# from PersonalWebsiteDemo when forking otherwise you will get an error
git clone https://github.com/[Your GitHub Account]/PersonalWebsite.git

# if you plan to use your own workflow then use the original one
git clone https://github.com/Stefanotuv/PersonalWebsiteDemo.git
----

1)  Install nodejs

curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

restart termninal

cd frontend
# --- in the frontend folder
nvm install --lts

npm install

2) install the virtual env

cd [path to venvironments]/
python3 -m venv venvpersonalwebsite
source venvpersonalwebsite/bin/activate

3) set up django
# Upgrade pip and install Python dependencies
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt

4) copy the variables .env

5) run django

python manage.py runserver 0.0.0.0/8000